1
00:00:42,625 --> 00:00:46,004
SOLD OUT ON YOU

2
00:01:05,023 --> 00:01:05,857
Okay.

3
00:01:08,610 --> 00:01:11,946
Might as well do as the residents
do, even if it's unfair. Have it

4
00:01:12,030 --> 00:01:14,616
your way, I'm leaving.

5
00:01:24,584 --> 00:01:25,794
What? What's that?

6
00:01:29,964 --> 00:01:34,052
What? What the-- What's happening? What's
wrong with my car?

7
00:01:36,513 --> 00:01:39,808
Knock it off with that stupid thing.
I'm trying to back up! Wow, that

8
00:01:39,891 --> 00:01:42,393
guy is nuts. Yikes.

9
00:01:48,733 --> 00:01:49,609
Come on, really?

10
00:02:16,803 --> 00:02:19,806
-Are you moving or what?
-There's space for you to squeeze through.

11
00:02:19,889 --> 00:02:22,225
Wait, you can't leave your car here
like that.

12
00:02:23,560 --> 00:02:26,729
I hate it to say it, but I have
some business to see to. So do what

13
00:02:26,813 --> 00:02:29,232
you need to do to get around. Have a nice
day.

14
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:30,358
Wait.

15
00:02:30,441 --> 00:02:36,406
Oh, I forgot. Uh, it's an expensive car.
So try to be careful, okay?

16
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:41,035
Wait. Hey! Hey!

17
00:02:43,037 --> 00:02:44,914
Now where is that mushroom farm?

18
00:04:10,208 --> 00:04:11,709
Where in the world is it?

19
00:04:22,512 --> 00:04:25,723
Not so bad if I walk like this.
Jesus, what am I doing here? Ow,

20
00:04:25,807 --> 00:04:28,518
careful. Ah, it hurts.

21
00:04:42,865 --> 00:04:44,200
Why are you following me?!

22
00:04:45,118 --> 00:04:47,203
-What?
-I asked why are you following me!

23
00:04:47,287 --> 00:04:48,538
This is where I'm headed!

24
00:04:54,877 --> 00:04:56,587
Pretty sure you're following me.

25
00:05:17,108 --> 00:05:17,942
Stop.

26
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:22,739
I knew it. You are following me.

27
00:05:23,823 --> 00:05:24,907
No, this is my route.

28
00:05:25,742 --> 00:05:29,037
This certainly is new. I'm usually
chased after by men in sports cars,

29
00:05:29,120 --> 00:05:32,582
but being chased in a tractor is
something else. So points for that.

30
00:05:32,665 --> 00:05:36,169
That being said, I'm here because
I have a very important meeting.

31
00:05:36,252 --> 00:05:42,675
Therefore, I'm asking you once again,
stop getting in my way.

32
00:05:44,802 --> 00:05:45,636
Listen…

33
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:49,682
Ugh, can you just stop? Oh, actually,
wait! Uh, I'm looking for the mushroom

34
00:05:49,766 --> 00:05:51,976
-farm.
-Of course.

35
00:05:53,061 --> 00:05:54,604
Can you tell me where it is?

36
00:05:58,816 --> 00:06:00,985
That way? Where? That way?

37
00:06:01,069 --> 00:06:03,029
No, step aside so I can get to my farm!

38
00:06:06,366 --> 00:06:07,200
What the--

39
00:06:10,661 --> 00:06:16,376
You're a-- You're a complete animal! Hey!
Hey!

40
00:06:21,172 --> 00:06:23,216
Mushrooms! That's gotta be it!

41
00:06:23,716 --> 00:06:29,514
Wait, sir! Hold on! Wait just a second!
Please! Hold on! Come back!

42
00:06:33,643 --> 00:06:34,477
Sir.

43
00:06:39,649 --> 00:06:42,777
Wait, so it can go in reverse? I knew it!

44
00:06:45,279 --> 00:06:48,491
You lied to me! You said it couldn't
reverse.

45
00:06:50,243 --> 00:06:51,077
Spit it out.

46
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:54,080
Um, is that where your mushrooms
are grown? Can I talk with the owner of

47
00:06:54,163 --> 00:06:55,206
the farm?

48
00:06:55,289 --> 00:06:56,290
They're not here!

49
00:06:57,458 --> 00:07:00,503
Uh, hold on! Could you at least
check before you send me away?

50
00:07:00,586 --> 00:07:03,506
If they were home, they still
wouldn't want to see you.

51
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:06,884
So when do they plan on working today?

52
00:07:06,968 --> 00:07:08,136
Won't be for a long time.

53
00:07:08,219 --> 00:07:09,053
Huh?

54
00:07:10,221 --> 00:07:11,055
What the…

55
00:07:11,139 --> 00:07:13,850
Uh, well, could you just relay a message
in that case?

56
00:07:15,893 --> 00:07:19,063
Fine. I'll tell them that a spoiled
girl with no manners whatsoever

57
00:07:19,147 --> 00:07:21,566
came by to see them.

58
00:07:22,066 --> 00:07:24,485
Ah., yes. I was rude earlier because
I'm new here.

59
00:07:24,569 --> 00:07:27,238
For your information, they despise
fake people.

60
00:07:29,282 --> 00:07:36,205
Just listen for a second. Uh, I run
a show with HIT. My name is Dam Ye-jin.

61
00:07:42,628 --> 00:07:44,505
HIT HOME SHOPPING
HOST DAM YE-JIN

62
00:07:50,595 --> 00:07:51,679
Wait. Please?

63
00:07:54,140 --> 00:07:55,391
Sorry, could-- Could you…

64
00:07:57,602 --> 00:08:01,939
Where are you going? Oh, come on.
What's that?

65
00:08:05,818 --> 00:08:10,656
Oh. Oh. come on. What an absolute jerk.

66
00:08:15,828 --> 00:08:16,787
Uh, seriously?!

67
00:08:52,615 --> 00:08:54,909
It's pretty dry today, so spray them
down.

68
00:08:54,992 --> 00:08:56,994
-On it.
-You got it.

69
00:08:57,078 --> 00:08:58,913
-Be gentle, okay?
-Yes, boss.

70
00:09:08,297 --> 00:09:09,257
Hello, Mr. Park.

71
00:09:13,094 --> 00:09:16,222
Oh, hey, Mechoori. You don't usually come
in 'til later.

72
00:09:16,305 --> 00:09:18,349
You missed an entire box of mushrooms.

73
00:09:18,849 --> 00:09:20,768
Oh, no. I forgot.

74
00:09:21,269 --> 00:09:24,272
I have asked you time and again to
pay more attention when you're working.

75
00:09:24,355 --> 00:09:27,024
Isn't quality control part of your job,
Mr. Park?

76
00:09:27,108 --> 00:09:30,695
I just wanted to have a little music,
so they'll grow faster. You know?

77
00:09:30,778 --> 00:09:33,322
-Ah, Kwang-mo's getting chewed out. I knew
-The music creates sound waves that

78
00:09:33,406 --> 00:09:35,324
-this would happen eventually.
-increase the plants' metabolism, not to

79
00:09:35,408 --> 00:09:37,785
-mention it drives the insects away.
-Mr. Park.

80
00:09:38,369 --> 00:09:41,956
These will be used for cosmetics and
medicine. I will not tolerate this

81
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:43,666
behavior on my farm, got it?

82
00:09:43,749 --> 00:09:44,792
Uh… ok.

83
00:09:45,501 --> 00:09:47,795
I promise. I'll be careful from now on.

84
00:09:47,878 --> 00:09:48,838
Power on.

85
00:09:54,385 --> 00:09:57,471
This is your final warning. Next time,
I won't be so patient.

86
00:09:59,223 --> 00:10:05,104
-So, so, sorry about that. I'm sorry!
-Mr. Park!

87
00:10:08,983 --> 00:10:11,819
So are these the mushrooms that look
like white flowers?

88
00:10:12,403 --> 00:10:13,279
You're still here?

89
00:10:13,362 --> 00:10:17,033
I was about to leave. Hey-- Hey,
do you have any spare shoes I could buy?

90
00:10:17,116 --> 00:10:17,950
I'll pay anything.

91
00:10:18,034 --> 00:10:19,035
No, sorry.

92
00:10:19,118 --> 00:10:22,330
Oh, don't be like that. Please, I'm
begging you, my feet are killing me.

93
00:10:22,413 --> 00:10:23,664
I can't wear these heels.

94
00:10:27,168 --> 00:10:30,504
You're not going to force me to
walk around with these blisters now,

95
00:10:30,588 --> 00:10:31,964
are you? Please?

96
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:38,888
Can I at least have a plastic bag or
something?

97
00:10:39,597 --> 00:10:41,015
Why would you run in heels anyway?

98
00:10:41,098 --> 00:10:45,102
What do you expect? I can't miss an
opportunity to meet the owner, you know?

99
00:10:45,186 --> 00:10:47,021
I mean, I'd run miles if I had to.

100
00:10:53,361 --> 00:10:54,195
This way.

101
00:11:00,576 --> 00:11:04,413
Don't worry about paying. Just grab a
pair and leave. But if you don't leave

102
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:08,125
this place, I'm reporting you to the
police for trespassing.

103
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:11,587
Ah.

104
00:11:13,798 --> 00:11:14,715
There's more here.

105
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:19,720
Uh, wait, I-- I-- I can't wear any of
these!

106
00:11:21,847 --> 00:11:22,932
Oh, shit.

107
00:11:31,691 --> 00:11:35,361
Ugh, I can't wear these. They're
disgusting.

108
00:11:51,252 --> 00:11:52,211
I am Dam Ye-jin.

109
00:11:53,462 --> 00:11:56,382
I will get my hands on some mushrooms,
hell or high water.

110
00:12:03,514 --> 00:12:06,016
My God. What are they doing?

111
00:12:11,605 --> 00:12:14,567
But-- But those two are stealing.

112
00:12:17,111 --> 00:12:20,865
Oh, okay. You go ahead, the farm owner
will love to hear about this. I'm so

113
00:12:20,948 --> 00:12:21,782
on it.

114
00:12:28,622 --> 00:12:32,793
And out you come. Come one, come on.

115
00:12:33,669 --> 00:12:35,880
Okay, all done. All done.

116
00:12:36,797 --> 00:12:38,132
Wait. Let me see.

117
00:12:41,469 --> 00:12:42,303
Uh, why?

118
00:12:47,057 --> 00:12:50,644
There's a bit still left in there,
you've got to cut the whole thing out.

119
00:12:50,728 --> 00:12:53,689
Oh, whatever. It's not that big a deal if
there's a little left.

120
00:12:53,773 --> 00:12:54,774
Mr. Park.

121
00:12:55,566 --> 00:12:59,195
Anything left will sprout mold
and ruin it. The batch will be worthless.

122
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:01,697
Yes, okay.

123
00:13:09,663 --> 00:13:13,501
I have to get back. So finish these up
and please be more careful.

124
00:13:14,043 --> 00:13:16,504
Wait. I can't finish all these,
there's too many.

125
00:13:16,587 --> 00:13:17,755
What the-- Oh…

126
00:13:29,350 --> 00:13:35,648
Rose. Oh, my sweet Rose. I'm so happy to
see you. Let's get out of here.

127
00:13:39,819 --> 00:13:42,947
What happened to your mirror? Oh, no.
You poor thing!

128
00:13:44,532 --> 00:13:46,242
Wait, you can't leave your car here
like that.

129
00:13:46,325 --> 00:13:48,869
Do what you need to do to get around.
Have a nice day.

130
00:13:48,953 --> 00:13:49,787
Hey.

131
00:13:50,287 --> 00:13:57,211
The tractor! He actually smashed into
my car? That guy's a total… lunatic!

132
00:14:01,465 --> 00:14:02,299
Rose.

133
00:14:04,260 --> 00:14:05,719
Hey! Move your car!

134
00:14:08,305 --> 00:14:11,600
You city people think you can just
block the road? Move out of the

135
00:14:11,684 --> 00:14:15,187
way! What are you doing, blocking the
road on a hot day like today?

136
00:14:18,357 --> 00:14:21,944
Okay, it's not like there's only
one tractor here. What was I thinking,

137
00:14:22,027 --> 00:14:25,781
leaving my car here? I didn't even meet
the mushroom farm owner, and my car

138
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,616
got destroyed.

139
00:14:40,546 --> 00:14:44,133
I run a show on HIT. My name is
Dam Ye-jin.

140
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:54,935
Mechoori. Mechoori! What's he doing?
Hey, boss! You okay? You were spaced out.

141
00:14:57,313 --> 00:14:59,398
-Oh, yeah.
-Come here.

142
00:15:08,073 --> 00:15:09,491
CHANGSIK
HE DOESN'T BITE

143
00:15:11,118 --> 00:15:12,578
Ah, Changsik.

144
00:15:15,623 --> 00:15:19,043
-Oh, my.
-Oh, goodness. That can't be true. No.

145
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:20,753
Mechoori!

146
00:15:22,838 --> 00:15:24,506
-Somi!
-Mechoori!

147
00:15:24,590 --> 00:15:25,424
Sang-geum.

148
00:15:26,258 --> 00:15:27,092
Mechoori.

149
00:15:30,387 --> 00:15:33,057
Na Som. Why aren't you in school? Are you
okay?

150
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:35,434
Please don't tell my sister.

151
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:36,852
Just get on.

152
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:40,356
You're in big trouble, young lady.
You know what he's like, don't you?

153
00:15:40,439 --> 00:15:43,192
-Ugh, really. Fine. I'll go.
-Good.

154
00:15:43,692 --> 00:15:48,364
Wow, every time I go to the market,
you show up right when I need you to.

155
00:15:48,864 --> 00:15:51,283
Seriously? That's because he knows when
to come.

156
00:15:51,951 --> 00:15:53,077
It's okay, I was passing by.

157
00:15:53,160 --> 00:15:54,578
You always give them a ride.

158
00:15:55,412 --> 00:15:57,373
-Na Som.
-Okay, I'm going!

159
00:15:59,750 --> 00:16:00,876
Oh, my. That girl.

160
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,419
You can get off at the main road.

161
00:16:02,503 --> 00:16:03,337
Alright.

162
00:16:07,508 --> 00:16:11,136
Yes, hello. I need help. I'm stranded
in Deokpung Village in Anyong-gun.

163
00:16:11,220 --> 00:16:14,932
My rear wheel is stuck and the mirror
is broken. Oh, uh-- What? It'll take

164
00:16:15,015 --> 00:16:18,185
three hours? You don't understand,
I'm needed on TV, I'm a very

165
00:16:18,268 --> 00:16:19,269
important host.

166
00:16:22,189 --> 00:16:23,607
Okay. Guess I've no choice.

167
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:29,405
Think, Ye-jin. You have to get to
Seoul in four hours, which means--

168
00:16:29,488 --> 00:16:35,119
The bus! Let's see, Deokpung Village,
Anyong-gun.

169
00:16:35,202 --> 00:16:36,036
ANYOUNG, SEOUL

170
00:16:36,120 --> 00:16:37,246
The next bus to Seoul…

171
00:16:38,747 --> 00:16:40,207
INTERCITY BUS TIMETABLE
14:30, REGULAR, 19,000 WON

172
00:16:40,290 --> 00:16:41,375
Leaves at two-thirty!

173
00:16:41,875 --> 00:16:43,335
In thirty minutes! Oh, no.

174
00:16:50,884 --> 00:16:51,719
Come on.

175
00:18:16,136 --> 00:18:17,596
Hold on! Help me!

176
00:18:20,265 --> 00:18:22,935
-Excuse me, please! Wait, please!
-Such a lovely day!

177
00:18:23,018 --> 00:18:23,852
It sure is!

178
00:18:24,520 --> 00:18:26,855
-It's so beautiful out, perfect sunshine.
-Hey! Wait, please!

179
00:18:26,939 --> 00:18:28,857
-Absolutely right!
-It's so nice out.

180
00:18:28,941 --> 00:18:33,695
-Hey! Wait! Please!
-Oh, look. Look at those clouds.

181
00:18:34,863 --> 00:18:36,949
Oh, goodness. So refreshing.

182
00:18:37,032 --> 00:18:38,075
Wait!

183
00:18:40,911 --> 00:18:42,496
Uh, my allergies are killing
me right now.

184
00:18:42,579 --> 00:18:46,125
Look at that. Look at all the
clouds move. It's sunny. Mm-hmm. Come on.

185
00:18:46,208 --> 00:18:47,459
The flowers are in bloom.

186
00:18:49,211 --> 00:18:50,462
Wait! Hey!

187
00:18:53,382 --> 00:18:59,346
Behind you! I need a ride! Just to the
bus terminal, please! Hey!

188
00:19:08,480 --> 00:19:09,439
I love this breeze!

189
00:19:10,858 --> 00:19:12,568
Hey, hey, hey! Stop the tractor!

190
00:19:12,651 --> 00:19:14,111
Oh, oh! Oh, no, Mechoori, stop at once!

191
00:19:14,194 --> 00:19:15,654
Oh, no! What in the world is going on?

192
00:19:15,737 --> 00:19:18,907
Oh! Oh! Stop driving, Mechoori!
Aren't you listening? Stop now!

193
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:21,910
Oh, I hope she isn't hurt! Oh no!

194
00:19:21,994 --> 00:19:23,996
I said stop the tractor this instant!

195
00:19:24,079 --> 00:19:25,873
She needs our help! Is she alright?

196
00:19:25,956 --> 00:19:27,374
Where did she come from?

197
00:19:36,842 --> 00:19:37,718
Ow, that hurts.

198
00:20:00,073 --> 00:20:01,325
Can I help you with that?

199
00:20:02,576 --> 00:20:03,410
Huh?

200
00:20:06,747 --> 00:20:08,081
Thought I was falling, so…

201
00:20:19,301 --> 00:20:20,802
Oh, my goodness! Are you alright?

202
00:20:20,886 --> 00:20:21,887
Oh, I'm fine! I'm okay.

203
00:20:21,970 --> 00:20:23,513
Dearest me! What a sight!

204
00:20:23,597 --> 00:20:25,599
Wow, they sure are pretty in Seoul!

205
00:20:25,682 --> 00:20:31,188
Oh, that's so kind of you. Excuse me,
is the bus terminal far from here?

206
00:20:31,939 --> 00:20:34,524
No, the local bus can drop you
right there!

207
00:20:34,608 --> 00:20:38,487
What a relief. I'm so grateful. I was
scared I'd miss it.

208
00:20:41,573 --> 00:20:45,327
Oh, forgive me, ma'am. I just need to--
I'm so sorry. Pardon me.

209
00:20:53,961 --> 00:20:54,836
What's wrong?

210
00:20:56,463 --> 00:20:57,297
It was you!

211
00:21:00,425 --> 00:21:01,260
Sit back down.

212
00:21:01,343 --> 00:21:04,221
Oh, she's from Seoul. She's never
been on a tractor, that girl! She should

213
00:21:04,304 --> 00:21:05,180
sit in the front.

214
00:21:07,432 --> 00:21:08,267
Right.

215
00:21:09,059 --> 00:21:10,978
-My goodness, you're pretty.
-Oh, no.

216
00:21:16,191 --> 00:21:17,567
You stopped at the exact right spot.

217
00:21:17,651 --> 00:21:18,944
Amazing how he can do that.

218
00:21:19,027 --> 00:21:20,821
He's got braking down to a science.

219
00:21:20,904 --> 00:21:22,114
It might rain tonight.

220
00:21:22,197 --> 00:21:23,615
Oh, is that so? It doesn't look like…

221
00:21:23,699 --> 00:21:25,534
So just come back if it's slow today.

222
00:21:25,617 --> 00:21:26,994
Don't you put your health at risk.
Promise me that.

223
00:21:27,077 --> 00:21:29,496
-Yeah, of course. Thank you.
-Alright, let's go.

224
00:21:31,832 --> 00:21:32,708
Oh, I'm fine.

225
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:34,584
Well, I'm not. Help me down!

226
00:21:34,668 --> 00:21:35,669
Oh, what a gentlemen.

227
00:21:35,752 --> 00:21:37,587
Oh, thank you. Oh, goodness.

228
00:21:37,671 --> 00:21:39,047
Over here, Sang-geum.

229
00:21:42,050 --> 00:21:45,387
Come on. Alright, let's go.

230
00:21:54,771 --> 00:21:57,941
-Ah, it's good to sit. It's so nice out.
-Bag is heavy today.

231
00:21:58,734 --> 00:22:00,986
You'll be getting an invoice for
the damages.

232
00:22:02,612 --> 00:22:04,197
Come over here, darling.

233
00:22:04,281 --> 00:22:05,157
Yes, ma'am.

234
00:22:07,117 --> 00:22:07,951
Here it comes.

235
00:22:13,665 --> 00:22:15,459
-Hello, ladies.
-Hurry, hurry!

236
00:22:15,542 --> 00:22:16,752
Let's go.

237
00:22:16,835 --> 00:22:18,795
-Okay, let's go. Hurry up, we've got
-Just a second.

238
00:22:18,879 --> 00:22:21,673
To get going.
What's with all the bags? Jeez.

239
00:22:21,757 --> 00:22:22,591
Hurry.

240
00:22:22,674 --> 00:22:23,759
-Oh, dear.
-Let's go.

241
00:22:25,135 --> 00:22:25,969
Finally.

